''See also [[Stan]]''
==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*staina-'', from Indo-European ''*stāi-no-, *stī-no-'' (a suffixed form of ''*stāi-'' ‘be solid, crowd together’).  Cognate with Old Frisian [[sten|stēn]], Old Saxon [[sten|stēn]] (Dutch [[steen]]), Old High German [[stein]] (German [[Stein]]), Old Norse [[steinn]] (Swedish [[sten]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐍄𐌰𐌹𐌽𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[στιον|στῖον]] ‘pebble’, Slavic ''*stēnā-'' (Russian [[стена]] ‘wall’).

